{"posts":[{"title":"各种积分","text":"高斯积分$$\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}e^{-x^{2}}dx$$ 设$I(t)={(\\int_{0}^{t}e^{-x^{2}}dx)}^2$, 则求 $$\\lim\\limits_{t \\to +\\infty}I(t)$$ $$I^{‘}(t) = 2(\\int_{0}^{t}e^{-x^{2}}dx)e^{-t^2} = 2\\int_{0}^{t}e^{-x^2-t^2}dx = 2\\int_{0}^{1}2te^{(y^2+1)t^2}dy$$ $$\\frac{dI(t)}{dt} = \\frac{\\int_0^1\\frac{e^{-(y^2+1)t^2}}{-(y^2+1)}dy}{dt}$$ $$I(t) = \\int_0^1\\frac{e^{-(y^2+1)t^2}}{-(y^2+1)}+C$$ $$I(0)=\\int_0^1\\frac{-1}{y^2+1}dy+C = -\\frac{\\pi}{4} + C=0,C=\\frac{\\pi}{4}$$ $$I(t) = \\int_0^1\\frac{e^{-(y^2+1)t^2}}{-(y^2+1)}+\\frac{\\pi}{4}$$ $$\\lim\\limits_{t \\to +\\infty}I(t)=0+\\frac{\\pi}{4} = \\frac{\\pi}{4}$$ $$\\therefore\\int_{0}^{+\\infty}e^{-x^{2}}dx=\\frac{\\sqrt{\\pi}}{2}$$","link":"/2023/12/28/%E5%90%84%E7%A7%8D%E7%A7%AF%E5%88%86/"}],"tags":[{"name":"微积分","slug":"微积分","link":"/tags/%E5%BE%AE%E7%A7%AF%E5%88%86/"}],"categories":[],"pages":[]}